President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Alabama due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from December 12-18, 2009. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The affected counties include Barbour, Butler, Clarke, Coffee, Conecuh, Covington, Crenshaw, Dale, Escambia, Geneva, Henry, and Pike. Michael Bolch has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.